#AI

White House Releases AI Bill of Rights Blueprint

The White House Office of Science and Technology Policy (OSTP) has identified the use of technology, data, and automated systems as among the greatest challenges posed to democracy today and as a result, it has proposed an AI Bill of Rights. OSTP stated that too often, these tools are used to limit our opportunities and prevent our access to critical resources or services, however, automated systems have also brought about extraordinary benefits, revolutionizing global industries, and driving important decisions across sectors. The Blueprint for an AI Bill of Rights is a set of five principles that are aimed to guide the design, use, and deployment of automated systems to protect the rights of the American public in the age of artificial intelligence.

 

 

#Crypto

Artist Rhett Mankind Uses $69 and ChatGPT To Create a $45M Meme Coin

Like any other meme coin, Turbo started out as a joke but quickly came to embody much more symbolizing the state of the market, forming a community, and acting as a sort of performative art. At the intersection of art, artificial intelligence (AI), and the realm of crypto degeneracy lies a new meme coin by the name of Turbo, which just days after its launch has reached a market cap of nearly $50 billion USD. Development of the coin began on April 24, when digital artist Rhett Mankind consulted ChatGPT to make the next great meme coin with a fitting budget of just $69 USD.

 

 

#HumanResources

IBM plans to replace 7,800 jobs with AI over time, pauses hiring certain positions

IBM CEO Krishna said that hiring in back-office functions like human resources will be suspended or slowed, affecting roughly 26,000 non-customer-facing roles. That will include not replacing current roles vacated by attrition. "I could easily see 30 percent of that getting replaced by AI and automation over a five-year period," Bloomberg quoted Krisha as saying in an interview.

 

 

#Music

Grimes Unveils Software to Mimic Her Voice, Offering 50-50 Royalties for Commercial Use

Grimes has unveiled an AI voice software, Elf.Tech. The beta software invites you to record or upload vocals for regurgitation in Grimes own voice, employing similar technology to Holly Herndons Holly+. Artists can commercially release the results in exchange for half of any master-recording royalties. Grimes announced a pair of new songs, Music for Machines and I Wanna Be Software, in tandem with the launch, though their release date has not been set.

 

 

#Robotics

Robot Dog Spot, Empowered by ChatGPT, Has Just Learned to Speak

Boston Dynamics, the robotics firm known for creating complex and intelligent machines, has just added another impressive feat to its repertoire. They have used ChatGPT to give their robot dog Spot the ability to communicate with humans via speech. This feat has been accomplished with a combination of natural language processing capabilities and machine learning techniques.

 

 

#Metaverse

Bebe Rexha Launches Her Metaverse, Bebeverse

Multi-platinum singer Bebe Rexha introduces her metaverse space dubbed Bebeverse. The initiative celebrates the release of her highly-anticipated third album entitled Bebe.To develop the virtual world, Warner Records, where Rexha is signed, partnered with TerraZero. The Vancouver-based company helps brands and businesses get into the metaverse while offering bespoke solutions and activations. When entering Rexhas virtual world, users transform into personalized Bebe avatars. Following this, they can join other Bebes in a disco-inspired virtual space filled with colorful party lights.
